T1  - When Others Retire Early: What About Me?
AU  - Mollica, Kelly A.
AU  - DeWitt, Rocki-Lee
Y1  - 2000/12/01
PY  - 2000
DA  - 2000/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/1556335
DO  - 10.5465/1556335
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 1068
EP  - 1075
VL  - 43
IS  - 6
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - We studied the reactions to an early retirement program of 668 employees of a large organization who were ineligible for the program. Specifically, we examined the influence of perceptions of the generosity of the organization's assistance to retirees (caretaking) on the remaining employees' intentions to quit. Findings contrasted with those from research on layoff survivors: perceptions of overly generous caretaking were associated with increased intentions to quit, particularly among more tenured employees.
AB  - We studied the reactions to an early retirement program of 668 employees of a large organization who were ineligible for the program. Specifically, we examined the influence of perceptions of the generosity of the organization's assistance to retirees (caretaking) on the remaining employees' intentions to quit. Findings contrasted with those from research on layoff survivors: perceptions of overly generous caretaking were associated with increased intentions to quit, particularly among more tenured employees.
